Five major football conference commissioners have asked the NCAA to relax some requirements to compete in Division I for four years, including the minimum number of sports a school must sponsor.
The College World Series is one of many NCAA events that have been canceled due to the coronavirus pandemic.
MAC Commissioner Jon Steinbrecher told the AP the request was to “build flexibility into the decision-making process” schools will be facing.
► Once every two years on a rolling basis, average at least 15,000 in actual or paid attendance for all home football games.
The NCAA and its schools have already taken a huge financial hit with the cancellation of the men’s basketball tournament in March.